===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|艸|盍|c1=s|t1=grass|c2=p|ls=psc}} — a thatch.

{{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|盍}} is the original character for the “cover” sense. However, because this original character was borrowed to mean “why not”, the scope of senses for {{lang-lite|zh|sc=Hani|蓋}} expanded to include the “cover” sense (and its extended meanings).

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*(g/k)wap|t=to cover, incubate, hatch}}. Within Chinese, compare:
* {{och-l|盍|to join, unite; door leaf}}
* {{och-l|閤|small gate}}
* {{och-l|蛤|oyster, mussel}}
* {{och-l|合|to join, unite; harmony; to close, shut}}
* {{och-l|洽|to unite, assemble; to accord with}}
* {{och-l|翕|united, harmonious}}
Outside of Sinitic, cognate with {{cog|lus|tr=hûap|t=to include, to take in, to cover, to embrace, to apply to}}. The Sino-Tibetan root is likely [[allofam]]ic with {{cog|tbq-pro|*ʔup|t=idem}}, the latter whence {{cog|my|အုပ်|t=to cover}} (STEDT).

